Reports suggest that the 3.7 magnitude earthquake was felt as far Port Shepstone on the South Coast to Durban. DURBAN - A tremor that lasted about 10 seconds was felt in KwaZulu-Natal just before 1:30 pm on Thursday. No major health hazards were reported but several people took to social media to share their experiences. Reports suggest that the 3.7 magnitude earthquake was felt as far Port Shepstone on the South Coast to Durban.   